Does Travel Broaden The Mind ?  There are so many reasons to pack a bag and go travelling .Whether itâ€™s the opportunity to meet new people, to immerse yourself in new experiences In this Journal essay I will be discussing a few point son why I believe travel broadens the mind .  Firstly , We gain a greater understanding of ourselves as aspecies when we travel to other countries and experience their social, cultural, political and architectural developments in relation to our own. By travelling, we get a clearer sense of where we come from, what we stand for and who we are in relation to others. Secondly, Travel broadens our minds because we can see a different way of doing things. Â We tend to accept the norm and like the way things are done because that is the only way we know. Â When you travel, it humbles you. Â You see that things can be done differently. Lastly, travel allows us to see how fortunate we are when compared to other people. When we go to third world countries and see how people live there and think back , we realise how fortunate we are to consume the food we do , live the way we live . Travelling thus allows us to appreciate what we have and learn to treasure the lives god has given us .
